<h1>Register to The Gossip Project !</h1>
<form action="/registration" method="post">
  <div class="form-group">
    <label for="formGroupExampleInput">Nickname</label>
    <input name="name" type="text" class="form-control" id="formGroupExampleInput" placeholder="Enter your Nickname">
    <small id="emailHelp" class="form-text text-muted">Warning, this is <strong>CASE SENSITIVE</strong></small>
  </div>
  <div class="form-group">
    <label for="exampleInputEmail1">Email address</label>
    <input name="email" type="email" class="form-control" id="exampleInputEmail1" aria-describedby="emailHelp" placeholder="Enter email">
    <small id="emailHelp" class="form-text text-muted">We'll definitely share your email with everybody.</small>
  </div>
  <div class="form-group">
    <label for="exampleInputPassword1">Password</label>
    <input name="password" type="password" class="form-control" id="exampleInputPassword1" placeholder="Password">
    <small id="emailHelp" class="form-text text-muted">Not hacker-proof, but who cares ?</small>
  </div>
  <div class="form-check">
    <input type="checkbox" class="form-check-input" id="exampleCheck1">
    <label class="form-check-label" for="exampleCheck1">By registering on this website, i accept that all of my personal stuff will be sold to a weird Chinese dude somewhere near the Bahamas, i'm perfectly aware of that, and it seems fine to me, so i will not sue the creator of this website (Which is in California anyway, so i cannot really do anything about that...)<br>Find more about it <a href="https://www.facebook.com/terms.php">here</a></label>
  </div>
  <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary">Submit</button>
  <input type="hidden" name="authenticity_token" value="<%= form_authenticity_token %>">
</form>